(1033, 1, 1030, NULL, 1, 'Durakh: Clan Culture and the Kor''vath', 'Clan Culture and the Kor''vath is filed as a secondary codex heading under Durakh and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to Syrath Prime and Nom''ara, while historical context from the Wandering Armada clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Field records from 2712 PF onward show local variation driven by gate traffic density, climate load, and military pressure. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, clan culture and the kor''vath is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. Planners therefore rank the domain as high consequence even when incident frequency appears low in public summaries.', NULL, NULL, 3),
(1034, 1, 1030, NULL, 1, 'Durakh: The Bombardment of Dur''ka', 'The Bombardment of Dur''ka is filed as a secondary codex heading under Durakh and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to Syrath Prime and Nom''ara, while historical context from the Wandering Armada clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Syrathi Elders frame the issue as a long-horizon stability problem that demands restraint, archives, and interspecies mediation. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, the bombardment of dur''ka is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. As a result, most command schools teach conservative escalation ladders with mandatory civilian-harm checkpoints.', NULL, NULL, 4),
(1035, 1, 1030, NULL, 1, 'Durakh: Durakh Mercenary Culture', 'Durakh Mercenary Culture is filed as a secondary codex heading under Durakh and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to Syrath Prime and Nom''ara, while historical context from the Wandering Armada clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Nomari engineering briefs emphasise redundancy and isolation because single-point failure remains the dominant operational risk. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, durakh mercenary culture is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. Planners therefore rank the domain as high consequence even when incident frequency appears low in public summaries.', NULL, NULL, 5);

