(1097, 1, 1095, NULL, 1, 'Veld: Veld-Chora Arrangement', 'Veld-Chora Arrangement is filed as a secondary codex heading under Veld and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to Syrath Prime and Nom''ara, while historical context from the Wandering Armada clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Vaekar doctrine formalised current practice after the Sundering and keeps response windows measured in minutes, not hours. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, veld-chora arrangement is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. The lesson repeated in every academy is simple: short-term victories fail when they ignore system-level second-order effects.', NULL, NULL, 2);

