(2021, 2, 2020, NULL, 1, 'Hegemony Intelligence: HID Structure', 'HID Structure is filed as a secondary codex heading under Hegemony Intelligence and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to Terran Hegemony and The Reach, while historical context from the New Providence clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Gate-adjacent populations report measurable psychological effects during sustained alert periods, especially among transit crews. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, hid structure is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. As a result, most command schools teach conservative escalation ladders with mandatory civilian-harm checkpoints.', NULL, NULL, 1),
