(2060, 2, NULL, 3, 0, 'The Ascendancy', 'The Ascendancy is catalogued by the Veil Compact Codex as a core humanity reference topic and is maintained by analysts on the Spire for active policy use. Current briefs link The Ascendancy to Terran Hegemony, Council of Ministers, and Hegemony Fleet Command, with recurring relevance to HID across both frontier and core systems. In post-Breach doctrine, the subject is no longer treated as static background lore but as an operational variable that shapes Accord readiness, diplomatic posture, and civilian confidence. Gate-adjacent populations report measurable psychological effects during sustained alert periods, especially among transit crews. Comparative reviews from 2698 PF to 2740 PF show that decision quality improves when planners evaluate technical limits, legal mandates, and cultural memory together rather than in isolation. Records from Arbiter debriefs and Directorate archives repeatedly highlight spillover effects into trade, migration, and recruitment pipelines whenever this domain is mishandled. Keth analysts note the strongest predictive signal comes from logistics, not ideology, because supply lines decide outcomes. The lesson repeated in every academy is simple: short-term victories fail when they ignore system-level second-order effects.', 72060, 22060, 7);

