    (id, category_id, parent_entry_id, requirement_id, entry_type, title, content, audio_id, image_id, sort_order)
VALUES
(2061, 2, 2060, NULL, 1, 'The Ascendancy: Founding Ideology', 'Founding Ideology is filed as a secondary codex heading under The Ascendancy and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to Terran Hegemony and The Reach, while historical context from the New Providence clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Reclamation teams continue to cross-reference Architect-era fragments with modern telemetry to close persistent evidentiary gaps. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, founding ideology is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. As a result, most command schools teach conservative escalation ladders with mandatory civilian-harm checkpoints.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(2062, 2, 2060, NULL, 1, 'The Ascendancy: Known Operations', 'Known Operations is filed as a secondary codex heading under The Ascendancy and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to Terran Hegemony and The Reach, while historical context from the New Providence clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Public education editions remove casualty imagery, yet service editions retain full after-action appendices for training. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, known operations is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. Planners therefore rank the domain as high consequence even when incident frequency appears low in public summaries.', NULL, NULL, 2),
(2063, 2, 2060, NULL, 1, 'The Ascendancy: Project Null-Born', 'Project Null-Born is filed as a secondary codex heading under The Ascendancy and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to Terran Hegemony and The Reach, while historical context from the New Providence clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Independent Arbiter assessments routinely classify local governance quality as the deciding factor in long-term recovery. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, project null-born is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. As a result, most command schools teach conservative escalation ladders with mandatory civilian-harm checkpoints.', NULL, NULL, 3),
(2064, 2, 2060, NULL, 1, 'The Ascendancy: The Ascendancy and the Hollow', 'The Ascendancy and the Hollow is filed as a secondary codex heading under The Ascendancy and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to Terran Hegemony and The Reach, while historical context from the New Providence clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Accord medical directorates maintain shared registries to track delayed exposure outcomes tied to Null-Matter contamination. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, the ascendancy and the hollow is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. Planners therefore rank the domain as high consequence even when incident frequency appears low in public summaries.', NULL, NULL, 4);

