VALUES
(3001, 3, 3000, NULL, 1, 'The Spire: History and Architect Origins', 'History and Architect Origins is filed as a secondary codex heading under The Spire and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to The Spire and Foundry District, while historical context from the member-state treaties clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Keth analysts note the strongest predictive signal comes from logistics, not ideology, because supply lines decide outcomes. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, history and architect origins is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. As a result, most command schools teach conservative escalation ladders with mandatory civilian-harm checkpoints.', NULL, NULL, 1),
(3002, 3, 3000, NULL, 1, 'The Spire: Districts and Layout', 'Districts and Layout is filed as a secondary codex heading under The Spire and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to The Spire and Foundry District, while historical context from the member-state treaties clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Vaekar doctrine formalised current practice after the Sundering and keeps response windows measured in minutes, not hours. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, districts and layout is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. Planners therefore rank the domain as high consequence even when incident frequency appears low in public summaries.', NULL, NULL, 2),
