    (id, category_id, parent_entry_id, requirement_id, entry_type, title, content, audio_id, image_id, sort_order)
VALUES
(4020, 4, NULL, NULL, 0, 'Ship Weapons', 'Ship Weapons is catalogued by the Veil Compact Codex as a core military reference topic and is maintained by analysts on the Spire for active policy use. Current briefs link Ship Weapons to Void Gates, Null Lancers, and Hierarchy battle groups, with recurring relevance to barrier doctrine across both frontier and core systems. In post-Breach doctrine, the subject is no longer treated as static background lore but as an operational variable that shapes Accord readiness, diplomatic posture, and civilian confidence. Syrathi Elders frame the issue as a long-horizon stability problem that demands restraint, archives, and interspecies mediation. Comparative reviews from 2698 PF to 2740 PF show that decision quality improves when planners evaluate technical limits, legal mandates, and cultural memory together rather than in isolation. Records from Arbiter debriefs and Directorate archives repeatedly highlight spillover effects into trade, migration, and recruitment pipelines whenever this domain is mishandled. The Foundry district functions as a pressure valve where legal commerce, grey markets, and intelligence trade overlap. The lesson repeated in every academy is simple: short-term victories fail when they ignore system-level second-order effects.', 94020, 44020, 3);

