VALUES
(4060, 4, NULL, NULL, 0, 'Mercenary Organisations', 'Mercenary Organisations is catalogued by the Veil Compact Codex as a core military reference topic and is maintained by analysts on the Spire for active policy use. Current briefs link Mercenary Organisations to Void Gates, Null Lancers, and Hierarchy battle groups, with recurring relevance to barrier doctrine across both frontier and core systems. In post-Breach doctrine, the subject is no longer treated as static background lore but as an operational variable that shapes Accord readiness, diplomatic posture, and civilian confidence. Keth analysts note the strongest predictive signal comes from logistics, not ideology, because supply lines decide outcomes. Comparative reviews from 2698 PF to 2740 PF show that decision quality improves when planners evaluate technical limits, legal mandates, and cultural memory together rather than in isolation. Records from Arbiter debriefs and Directorate archives repeatedly highlight spillover effects into trade, migration, and recruitment pipelines whenever this domain is mishandled. Reclamation teams continue to cross-reference Architect-era fragments with modern telemetry to close persistent evidentiary gaps. The lesson repeated in every academy is simple: short-term victories fail when they ignore system-level second-order effects.', 94060, 44060, 7);

