(5043, 5, 5040, NULL, 1, 'AI and Synthetics: The Intelligence Prohibition Incident', 'The Intelligence Prohibition Incident is filed as a secondary codex heading under AI and Synthetics and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to Null-Matter and True AI prohibition, while historical context from the Architect relic interfaces clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Durakh clan records preserve contradictory oral histories, but all versions agree that strategic humiliation outlasts military defeat. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, the intelligence prohibition incident is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. As a result, most command schools teach conservative escalation ladders with mandatory civilian-harm checkpoints.', NULL, NULL, 3);

