(6061, 6, 6060, NULL, 1, 'Core Systems: Auris System (The Spire)', 'Auris System (The Spire) is filed as a secondary codex heading under Core Systems and serves as a practical briefing layer for commanders, diplomats, and investigators. The current synthesis ties the topic to Auris System and frontier colonies, while historical context from the survey expeditions clarifies why policy language remains deliberately conservative. Analysts emphasize that this subtopic cannot be read apart from infrastructure strain, legal jurisdiction boundaries, and the uneven administrative capacity of member worlds. Keth analysts note the strongest predictive signal comes from logistics, not ideology, because supply lines decide outcomes. Recent audits found that outcomes improve when local actors share telemetry early, standardize terminology, and publish cross-species compatibility guidance before incidents escalate. In training doctrine, auris system (the spire) is used as a case study for balancing speed and restraint under uncertain intelligence conditions. As a result, most command schools teach conservative escalation ladders with mandatory civilian-harm checkpoints.', NULL, NULL, 1),
