(7090, 7, NULL, 2, 0, 'Historical Figures', 'Historical Figures is catalogued by the Veil Compact Codex as a core history reference topic and is maintained by analysts on the Spire for active policy use. Current briefs link Historical Figures to Great Silence, Awakening, and Founding Wars, with recurring relevance to Sundering across both frontier and core systems. In post-Breach doctrine, the subject is no longer treated as static background lore but as an operational variable that shapes Accord readiness, diplomatic posture, and civilian confidence. Nomari engineering briefs emphasise redundancy and isolation because single-point failure remains the dominant operational risk. Comparative reviews from 2698 PF to 2740 PF show that decision quality improves when planners evaluate technical limits, legal mandates, and cultural memory together rather than in isolation. Records from Arbiter debriefs and Directorate archives repeatedly highlight spillover effects into trade, migration, and recruitment pipelines whenever this domain is mishandled. Cross-species standards now require explicit compatibility notes for dextro and levo biochemistry in all deployed systems. Planners therefore rank the domain as high consequence even when incident frequency appears low in public summaries.', 127090, 77090, 10);

