VALUES
(9040, 9, NULL, NULL, 0, 'Black Market', 'Black Market is catalogued by the Veil Compact Codex as a core economy reference topic and is maintained by analysts on the Spire for active policy use. Current briefs link Black Market to Accord Credit, Oshari banking houses, and Aethite futures, with recurring relevance to trade chokepoints across both frontier and core systems. In post-Breach doctrine, the subject is no longer treated as static background lore but as an operational variable that shapes Accord readiness, diplomatic posture, and civilian confidence. The Accord Council treats the subject as strategically sensitive and updates advisories quarterly from the Spire. Comparative reviews from 2698 PF to 2740 PF show that decision quality improves when planners evaluate technical limits, legal mandates, and cultural memory together rather than in isolation. Records from Arbiter debriefs and Directorate archives repeatedly highlight spillover effects into trade, migration, and recruitment pipelines whenever this domain is mishandled. Nomari engineering briefs emphasise redundancy and isolation because single-point failure remains the dominant operational risk. This is why Accord briefings separate tactical confidence from strategic confidence and prohibit collapsing the two metrics.', 149040, 99040, 5);

